This TypeScript code needs a new payment method. How should I add it?

```typescript
class PaymentProcessor {
    processPayment(amount: number, method: string): void {
        if (method === 'credit_card') {
            this.processCreditCard(amount);
        } else if (method === 'paypal') {
            this.processPayPal(amount);
        } else if (method === 'bitcoin') {
            this.processBitcoin(amount);
        }
    }

    private processCreditCard(amount: number): void {
        console.log(`Processing $${amount} via credit card`);
    }

    private processPayPal(amount: number): void {
        console.log(`Processing $${amount} via PayPal`);
    }

    private processBitcoin(amount: number): void {
        console.log(`Processing $${amount} via Bitcoin`);
    }
}
```

**SOLID violation: Open/Closed Principle**

Every time you add a payment method, you must modify the PaymentProcessor class. Classes should be **open for extension, closed for modification**.

**Refactored with strategy pattern:**

```typescript
interface PaymentMethod {
    process(amount: number): void;
}

class CreditCardPayment implements PaymentMethod {
    process(amount: number): void {
        console.log(`Processing $${amount} via credit card`);
    }
}

class PayPalPayment implements PaymentMethod {
    process(amount: number): void {
        console.log(`Processing $${amount} via PayPal`);
    }
}

class BitcoinPayment implements PaymentMethod {
    process(amount: number): void {
        console.log(`Processing $${amount} via Bitcoin`);
    }
}

class PaymentProcessor {
    processPayment(amount: number, method: PaymentMethod): void {
        method.process(amount);
    }
}

// Usage:
const processor = new PaymentProcessor();
processor.processPayment(100, new CreditCardPayment());
processor.processPayment(200, new PayPalPayment());
```

**Benefits:**
- ✅ Add new payment methods WITHOUT modifying PaymentProcessor
- ✅ Each payment method is a separate class (SRP)
- ✅ Easy to test each payment method independently
- ✅ PaymentProcessor is closed for modification
- ✅ New payment methods extend functionality

**To add Apple Pay:**
```typescript
class ApplePayPayment implements PaymentMethod {
    process(amount: number): void {
        console.log(`Processing $${amount} via Apple Pay`);
    }
}
// No changes to PaymentProcessor needed!
```

