**Clean Code issue: Function doing too much**

This function has multiple responsibilities: validation, normalization, tier calculation, database operations, email, logging.

**Refactored into focused functions:**

```typescript
function validateUserData(data: any): void {
    if (!data.email || !data.email.includes('@')) {
        throw new Error('Invalid email');
    }
    if (!data.age || data.age < 18) {
        throw new Error('Must be 18+');
    }
}

function normalizeUserData(data: any): { email: string; name: string } {
    return {
        email: data.email.toLowerCase().trim(),
        name: data.name.trim(),
    };
}

function calculateUserTier(purchaseTotal: number): string {
    if (purchaseTotal > 1000) return 'gold';
    if (purchaseTotal > 500) return 'silver';
    return 'bronze';
}

function processUserData(data: any): void {
    validateUserData(data);

    const normalized = normalizeUserData(data);
    const tier = calculateUserTier(data.purchaseTotal);

    const user = {
        ...normalized,
        age: data.age,
        tier,
    };

    db.insert('users', user);
    emailService.send(user.email, 'Welcome!', `Welcome ${user.name}`);
    logger.info(`User created: ${user.email}`);
}
```

**Benefits:**
- ✅ Each function has single, clear purpose
- ✅ Easy to test each function independently
- ✅ Validation logic is reusable
- ✅ Tier calculation is testable in isolation
- ✅ Main function reads like pseudocode

